{{Quick Guide}}

==Details==
{{Quest details page|In Aid of the Myreque}}

==Walkthrough==
===Starting out===
{{Checklist|
*Climb down the trapdoor behind the Canifis pub.
*Search the wall and enter the cave entrance just southeast.
*Talk to [[Veliaf Hurtz]]. {{Chat option|1I want to join your organisation.}}}}

===Patching up Burgh De Rott===
{{Needed|At least 1 piece of [[food]] you don't mind losing (5 pieces is recommended if running past [[ghasts]] without a [[druid pouch]]), a [[pickaxe]], a [[spade]], 1-5 [[buckets]], a [[hammer]], 44 [[nail]]s, 11 [[plank]]s, 1 [[swamp paste]], 3 tinderboxes, 10 bronze axes, 10 raw mackerels or 10 snails (depending on what is asked).<br/>If [[Shades of Mort'ton]] has been completed, a hammer, planks, and swamp paste can be purchased from [[Razmire Builders Merchants]] in [[Mort'ton]] and the tinderboxes, axes, and mackerels/snails can be brought noted then sold to [[Razmire General Store]] to unnote them. You '''cannot''' use the general store trick as an ironman.''
|recommended=[[Mort'ton teleport]] or [[fairy ring]] {{Fairycode|BIP}}}}

{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Florin]] through the gate to [[Burgh de Rott]].
*Put a piece of food into the open chest, then open the gate.
*Talk to [[Razvan]] near the pub. {{Chat option|4Are there any 'out of the way' places in here?}}
*Enter the pub, climb over the broken down wall, then use your pickaxe on the rubble blocking the trapdoor.
*Climb down and mine the rest of the [[Rubble (In Aid of the Myreque)|rubble]]. '''Anything you drop in the basement will be lost upon leaving.'''
*Use your spade on the remnants to fill the buckets. There is enough here to fill five buckets.
** Upon mining the rubble, you will find a [[plaster fragment]] and a [[dusty scroll]].
** The items dug up can be safely dropped, unless you need the [[nail]]s.
*When finished, use the buckets of rubble on the rubble pile outside the pub.
*Talk to Razvan again. {{Chat option|3I'd like to help fix up the town.}}
*Talk to [[Aurel]] in the general store to the north-east. {{Chat option|3I'd like to help fix up the town.}}
*Climb up the ladder right outside.
*Use 3 planks and 12 nails on the broken roof of the store.
*Climb back down and Use 3 planks on the damaged wall of the general store.
*Talk to Aurel again to get a [[Crate (In Aid of the Myreque)|crate]]. {{Chat option|3What should I do now?}}
**If you weren't able to bring all of the items, head to a bank now to get the remaining items for this section.
*Add 10 [[bronze axe]]s, 10 [[raw mackerel]]s '''or''' 10 [[snail]]s (depending on what is asked), and 3 [[tinderbox]]es to the crate.
*Talk to Aurel.
*Talk to [[Cornelius]] in the bank. {{Chat option|4What should I do now?}}
*Use a hammer with 2 planks, 1 swamp paste, and 8 nails on the broken bank booth
*Use a hammer with 3 planks and 12 nails on the damaged wall outside.
*Talk to Cornelius to recruit him. {{Chat option|4}}
}}
'''You now have access to the Burgh de Rott bank.'''

===Defending the village===
{{Needed|[[Hammer]], [[tinderbox]], 2 [[steel bar]]s, 1 [[coal]], [[Efaritay's aid]] or a [[silver weaponry]] such as a [[silver sickle (b)]], and some food for lower-levelled players.}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Razvan]]. {{Chat option|4What should I do now?}}
*Repair the furnace to the southeast. Use your steel bars, then coal, then tinderbox on the furnace.
*Talk to [[Gadderanks]] in the general store.
*Talk to the [[Vampyre Juvinate]] in the store.
*Talk to [[Wiskit]].
*Kill [[Gadderanks]] and the 2 juvinates (you'll need a silver weapon or Wolfbane dagger or [[Efaritay's aid]] to damage them).
*Talk to Gadderanks.
*Talk to Veliaf Hurtz.
}}

===Transporting Ivan===
{{Needed|Combat equipment, including [[silver weaponry]] or [[Efaritay's aid]] to defeat 2 level 75 or 4 level 50 Vampyre Juvinates. Deposit any [[follower]]s you have into your bank as Ivan Strom will refuse to leave if you have one, even in your inventory.''
|recommended=To give to Ivan Strom: [[Steel med helm]], [[Steel chainbody]], and [[Steel platelegs]], 15 pieces of cooked [[food]] ([[snail]], [[salmon]], [[Cooked slimy eel|slimy eel]], or [[stew]])}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to Veliaf Hurtz in the hideout where the quest started. (The room under the Canifis pub)
*Talk to [[Polmafi Ferdygris]].
**'''Highly ''Recommended'''''<nowiki/>'': Give [[Ivan Strom]] some food (he only takes snail, salmon, slimy eel, or stew) and steel armour (he only takes a steel med helm, steel chainbody, and steel platelegs) before leaving.''
{{Instance}}
*Talk to Ivan Strom to go on a simplified version of [[Temple Trekking]] and take either the short or long route. (you can't bring a pet - it must be banked!)
**Route 1 features two level 75 [[Vampyre Juvinate]]s, whereas route 2 features 4 level 50 Juvinates.
*Kill the [[Vampyre Juvinates]] before they can kill Ivan Strom.
**''Tip:'' ''Alternate your attacks between them so they stay focused on you. Also, it may be possible to talk to Ivan to prevent the vampyre from attacking him''
*After you're done escorting Ivan, talk to [[Drezel]] in the underground temple for a key. {{Chat option|1Veliaf told me about Ivandis.|1So, you're sure that Ivandis is buried here then?|2What proof do you have that Ivandis is buried here?|3What do you know about the history of this temple?|4Is there somewhere that I might get more information about Ivandis?|3The lives of those pitiful few left in Morytania could rest on this!}}
*Use the key on the keyhole on the eastern wall and climb down the trapdoor.
*Search the bookcases in the hidden room until you find [[The sleeping seven]] (The title of the book at the top when reading it is "The Sleeping Seven"). Read it.
}}

===The rod of Ivandis===
{{Needed|[[Hammer]], [[soft clay]], [[mithril bar]], [[silver bar]], a [[water rune]] or staff, a [[cosmic rune]], a cut [[sapphire]], and a [[rope]].|recommended=[[Teleport]]s to a [[furnace]] and back to [[Burgh de Rott]]}}
{{Checklist|
*Return to the room under the Canifis pub, then go to the blockaded cave entrance just south-east of the wall.
*Use a hammer on the wooden boards and enter the cave.
*Use your soft clay on the coffin to make a rod mould.
*Go to any furnace with your mould, a silver bar, a mithril bar and a sapphire, and craft a [[silvthrill rod]]. (Fairy ring {{Fairycode|dkr}} for [[Edgeville Furnace]].)
*Cast [[Lvl-1 Enchant]] on the rod.
*Use the rod on the well underneath the [[Paterdomus temple]] (where Drezel was) with a rope in your inventory. (Nearest fairy ring {{Fairycode|cks}})
*Return to the Burgh de Rott pub basement with the [[Rod of Ivandis]] (it must be in your inventory, not equipped), then speak to Veliaf. {{Chat option|1I have brought you the Rod of Ivandis!|1Yes, I've come to give the Rod of Ivandis to you!}}
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

==Rewards==
{{Quest rewards page|In Aid of the Myreque}}

==Required for completing==
Completion of In Aid of the Myreque is required for the following:
*[[Darkness of Hallowvale]]
*Medium tier of the [[Morytania Diary]]
{{In Aid of the Myreque}}
